<H1>The if statement</H1>

<P>The <SAMP>if</SAMP> statement uses the exit status of the given
command and conditionally executes the statements
following.  The general syntax is:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   if <EM>test</EM>
   then
      <EM>commands     </EM>(if condition is true)
   else
      <EM>commands     </EM>(if condition is false)
   fi
</PRE>

<P><SAMP>then</SAMP>, <SAMP>else</SAMP> and <SAMP>fi </SAMP>
are shell reserved words and as such
are only recognised after a newline or ; (semicolon).
Make sure that you end each <SAMP>if</SAMP> construct with a <SAMP>fi</SAMP>
statement.</P>

<P><SAMP>if</SAMP> statements may be nested:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   if ...
   then ...
   else if ...
       ...
     fi
   fi
</PRE>

<P>The <SAMP>elif</SAMP> statement can be used as shorthand for an
<SAMP>else if</SAMP> statement. For example:

<PRE WIDTH=80>   if ...
   then ...
   elif ...
     ...
   fi
</PRE>

